<DATELINE>
   MELBOURNE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Wesfarmers, the Australian fertiliser, chemicals and coal group, yesterday
reported a 88.7 per cent increase in profit after tax to ADollars 139.5m
(USDollars 102.6m) for the year ended June.
Sales, which rose 34 per cent to ADollars 2.3bn, were lifted mainly by the
