TelecomAsia, Thailand's second-biggest company by market capitalisation,
reported a net loss of Bt81.55m (Dollars 3.2m) in the first six months,
compared with a profit of Bt521.18m a year ago, writes William Barnes in
Bangkok.
Costs have risen sharply as TelecomAsia moves to supply 2m new lines in
Bangkok, the Thai capital.
