<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 94 / Observer: Naked ambition
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So what can you deduce about a politician from the clothes he wears? Too
much, one of the opposition socialists standing in Germany's October general
election has obviously decided. Accordingly, the bearded and
well-upholstered Thomas Kruger has decorated most of Berlin with his own
life-size image, unmodified by a stitch of clothing. Behind the bulging
flesh is 'an honest politician with nothing to hide'.
Funny, looks to the untrained eye more like another politico with an
over-developed ego . . .
</TEXT>
