<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 94 / Mideast peace talks rescue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JULIAN OZANNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JERUSALEM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Senior Israeli and Palestinian officials met in Egypt yesterday to rescue
peace negotiations from collapse amid mounting tension over speeding up
Palestinian self-rule to the West Bank and the unstable security situation
in the Gaza Strip, Julian Ozanne reports from Jerusalem. Mr Shimon Peres,
Israeli foreign minister, said before the meeting in the Mediterranean city
of Alexandria that 'the Palestinian side and we are struggling very hard so
that this thing will not collapse'. He said attacks on Israelis by
Palestinian militant and deteriorating economic conditions of Palestinians
in Gaza are 'threatening' the self-rule agreement.
