<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Prudential
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prudential Corporation's US subsidiary, Jackson National Life Insurance, saw
pre-tax profits fall from Dollars 118.5m to Dollars 71.6m (Pounds 46.1m) in
the six months to end-June. There was a further Dollars 4.6m from capital
gains against Dollars 55.1m.
Premiums dropped from Dollars 1.31bn to Dollars 1.07bn, though investment
income rose slightly from Dollars 665m to Dollars 703.9m.
</TEXT>
