<HEADLINE>
FT  17 AUG 94 / New building orders rise 15%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
New construction orders for the second quarter of the year rose 15 per cent
from the same period last year, government figures showed yesterday, Andrew
Jack writes.
Orders received by contractors for construction work were down 4 per cent
from this year's first quarter.
The figures, published by the Department of the Environment, are based on
the value of orders at existing prices adjusted to exclude normal seasonal
variations.
New orders in the private housing sector were 3 per cent lower in the second
quarter than in the first quarter and 21 per cent above the second quarter
last year.
The total value of new orders in June was Pounds 1.71m.
</TEXT>
